title: DeLorean - Radio Drama
description:
1 x 45 mins

Belfast in the 1970s was an unlikely place to set up a new factory to build a revolutionary sports car. But with massive injections of UK government cash, this is just what John DeLorean did - until it spectacularly failed a few years later.

This dramatised account looks at the story through the eyes of two fictional workers from either side of the religious divide
